p=\frac{6-x+1}{6}
m
P(\text{hitting exactly m times})=\frac{n!}{m!(n-m)!}p^m(1-p)^{n-m}
P(\text{hitting at least m times})=\sum\limits_{i=m}^n \frac{n!}{i!(n-i)!}p^i(1-p)^{n-i}
